{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 13:12:46.753070", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report – MPLS Network (bmv2)\n\nSummary\n- Topology: host_1 at switch_1 edge; host_2 and host_3 at switch_7 edge; core via switches 2–6.\n- Control plane: bmv2 P4 pipeline present on all switches with tables for ingress/egress border checks, IPv4 LPM, FEC-to-label, and MPLS forwarding.\n\n1) Anomaly Detection\n- End-to-end reachability: Normal. All tested host pairs communicate with 0% packet loss.\n  - host_1 ↔ host_2: RTT ~12–18 ms (consistent with multi-hop/MPLS traversal).\n  - host_1 ↔ host_3: RTT ~14–15 ms (consistent with MPLS path).\n  - host_2 ↔ host_3: RTT ~2–4 ms (both attached to switch_7; expected low latency).\n- No packet loss or obvious latency outliers observed.\n- MPLS dataplane behavior: Normal based on sampled switch logs; label push and label switching observed where expected; local traffic on switch_7 forwarded without MPLS as expected.\n\n2) Localization of Faulty Devices (if any)\n- No faulty devices identified. All observed devices forward traffic correctly:\n  - switch_1 (edge/LER for host_1): Applies MPLS encapsulation and forwards into the core; mpls_tbl hits and MPLS TTL decrement observed; egress border check correctly misses on core-facing port (NoAction), indicating it is not at egress border on that hop.\n  - switch_7 (edge/LER for host_2/host_3): On ingress from host-facing port (port 4), ingress-border flag set; FEC-to-label lookup for 10.7.2.2 (host_2) intentionally misses (local FEC), falling back to IPv4 LPM and forwarding locally without MPLS—expected behavior.\n\n3) Root Cause Identification\n- No service-impacting issue detected; therefore no root cause to identify.\n\nAdditional Findings and Notes\n- P4 pipeline inventory:\n  - All switches report the presence of MyIngress.ipv4_lpm, MyIngress.fec_to_label, MyIngress.mpls_tbl, and border-check tables in ingress/egress.\n- Runtime evidence from logs:\n  - switch_1: MPLS header setValid, label programmed, MyIngress.mpls_tbl hit (label 2), action MyIngress.mpls_forward executed, TTL decremented, forwarded out core port.\n  - switch_7: Ingress border classification on host-facing port; fec_to_label miss for local destination; ipv4_lpm hit and plain IPv4 forwarding—correct for on-switch local delivery.\n- Tooling limitations encountered (not a network issue):\n  - bmv2_table_dump invocations returned a SyntaxError via the tooling wrapper, and counter arrays returned empty. Despite this, live logs confirm correct table hits and actions; no indication of faulty dataplane behavior.\n\nConclusion\n- Overall network health: Good.\n- MPLS functionality: Operating as intended at ingress/LSR/egress roles observed.\n- No anomalies, misroutes, or losses detected; no devices localized as faulty; no root cause to report.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 10029, "output_tokens": 3177, "total_tokens": 13206, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 5888}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 2496}}}
